WEBVTT

00:00.895 --> 00:04.027
<i>- Previously on</i> The Resident...
- You're fired.

00:04.029 --> 00:05.746
You're afraid of me.

00:05.748 --> 00:06.897
<i>And you should be.</i>

00:06.899 --> 00:08.851
<i>KIM: Security will escort you out.</i>

00:08.853 --> 00:10.492
<i>MINA: If my sister has a child,</i>

00:10.494 --> 00:12.160
then that child becomes my family, too.

00:12.162 --> 00:14.029
Are you saying you'll
be my baby's godmother?

00:14.031 --> 00:16.053
<i>AUSTIN: You said yes?</i>
All right, so what's your plan

00:16.056 --> 00:18.011
if Adaku's baby becomes
your responsibility?

00:18.013 --> 00:19.093
I don't have one.

00:19.095 --> 00:22.561
<i>There was a learning
curve, but I mastered it.</i>

00:22.563 --> 00:24.357
Why don't you come
over to our place later?

00:24.359 --> 00:26.218
Uh, not tonight.

00:26.220 --> 00:27.526
<i>I'm tired.</i>

00:27.528 --> 00:30.029
<i>A little time alone with my thoughts.</i>

00:37.304 --> 00:40.186
<i>CONRAD: This incredible woman
had the ability to save a life</i>

00:40.188 --> 00:42.433
<i>right in front of me. And
I knew, in that moment,</i>

00:42.435 --> 00:43.876
<i>that I wanted to be a person</i>

00:43.878 --> 00:47.547
<i>who could jump out of
the car to help people.</i>

00:47.549 --> 00:49.483
<i>So that's what I do.</i>

00:56.149 --> 00:57.866
(EXHALES)

01:01.729 --> 01:04.397
NIC: Methodist Memorial
went with someone else.

01:04.399 --> 01:08.401
(SIGHS) Apparently they checked
in with my last employer.

01:08.403 --> 01:10.001
Red Rock has gotten you blacklisted

01:10.003 --> 01:11.682
from every hospital in Atlanta.

01:11.684 --> 01:13.166
I want to practice medicine,

01:13.168 --> 01:15.394
I'll have to find work out of town.

01:16.354 --> 01:18.228
Have a long-distance relationship

01:18.230 --> 01:20.471
or give up being a doctor.
This is what it's come to?

01:20.473 --> 01:21.829
No, it hasn't.

01:21.831 --> 01:24.877
We're gonna figure this out.

01:24.879 --> 01:26.454
You should go, you're gonna be late.

01:26.456 --> 01:28.122
Eh...

01:28.124 --> 01:29.382
(GROANS)

01:30.115 --> 01:31.470
(GRUNTS)

01:31.472 --> 01:33.529
You have any idea why
Reggie wanted to see you?

01:33.531 --> 01:35.670
No, he just said to meet him

01:35.672 --> 01:37.812
at the Georgia FC practice field.

01:37.814 --> 01:40.565
Is it bad that I had no idea
Atlanta has a soccer team?

01:41.587 --> 01:43.137
Yes.

01:43.139 --> 01:44.772
But I forgive you.

01:50.238 --> 01:52.572
(INDISTINCT CHATTER IN BACKGROUND)

01:52.574 --> 01:55.630
Well, hel-hello, good sir.

01:55.632 --> 01:57.450
Some tea and crumpets, perhaps?

01:57.452 --> 01:59.059
Ha. Very funny.

01:59.061 --> 02:01.230
I need to make a good
impression on my new attending.

02:01.232 --> 02:03.833
Ah, right, first day in
the dual residency program.

02:03.835 --> 02:05.449
Internal medicine this week. ER next.

02:05.451 --> 02:07.403
And then I go back and forth.

02:07.405 --> 02:10.788
IRVING: A foot in two
departments fundamentally at odds.

02:10.791 --> 02:13.130
Well, as a dual resident, I
can reach across the aisle,

02:13.132 --> 02:15.098
help each department
see how the other lives.

02:15.100 --> 02:16.286
If you say so.

02:16.288 --> 02:18.288
But lose the bow tie.

02:18.290 --> 02:19.766
You look like a chemistry professor

02:19.768 --> 02:21.125
who refuses to hand out As

02:21.127 --> 02:23.129
even when they're totally deserved.

02:23.131 --> 02:25.491
- That was oddly specific.
- I was really good at chemistry.

02:29.798 --> 02:32.057
Fine. You know what?

02:32.059 --> 02:33.651
Okay, baby girl.

02:33.653 --> 02:35.927
Your bottle is coming right up.

02:35.929 --> 02:39.347
(CRYING)

02:39.349 --> 02:42.071
<i>♪ The wheels on the bus
go round and round ♪</i>

02:42.073 --> 02:45.001
<i>♪ Round and round, round and round ♪</i>

02:45.003 --> 02:47.480
(SINGING ALONG): <i>♪ The horn on the
bus goes beep, beep, beep ♪</i>

02:47.482 --> 02:50.075
- (BOTTLE WARMER BEEPS)
- Shh...

02:50.077 --> 02:52.527
<i>♪ The horn on the bus
goes beep, beep, beep ♪</i>

02:52.529 --> 02:55.581
- <i>♪ All through the town ♪</i>
- (CHUCKLES)

02:55.583 --> 02:58.749
<i>♪ The baby on the bus
goes wah, wah, wah ♪</i>

02:58.751 --> 03:00.869
<i>♪ Wah, wah, wah, wah, wah, wah ♪</i>

03:00.871 --> 03:03.447
- Mm-hmm.
- <i>♪ The babies on the bus go wah, wah, wah ♪</i>

03:03.449 --> 03:06.350
(SINGING ALONG): <i>♪ All
through the town. ♪</i>

03:06.352 --> 03:08.352
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

03:11.715 --> 03:13.788
- Reggie.
- Dax.

03:13.790 --> 03:16.433
- What's good, Conrad?
- Yeah, good to see you.

03:16.435 --> 03:17.744
- Good to see you.
- Good to see you.

03:17.746 --> 03:20.320
I want you to meet
my mentee, Dax Ramsey.

03:20.322 --> 03:21.684
Yeah, rookie out of Memphis.

03:21.686 --> 03:23.866
You're supposed to be the
next face of the franchise.

03:23.868 --> 03:25.035
Yeah. That's the plan.

03:25.037 --> 03:26.519
If I can get my injuries under control.

03:26.521 --> 03:28.563
Today is Dax's first practice back.

03:28.565 --> 03:31.691
- He's recovering from a calf injury.
- Which feels fine, but...

03:31.693 --> 03:33.932
what worries me is I get
these cramps and injuries

03:33.934 --> 03:34.946
from the smallest things.

03:34.948 --> 03:37.289
The more conditioning I do,
the weaker I seem to get.

03:37.291 --> 03:39.130
The team doc, he ran a bunch of tests.

03:39.132 --> 03:41.882
Everything came back normal,
so he cleared Dax to play.

03:41.884 --> 03:44.037
But I keep telling him
there's something up with me.

03:44.039 --> 03:45.872
But he won't listen, so I asked Reggie

03:45.874 --> 03:47.666
if he knew a doctor who could
give me a second opinion.

03:47.668 --> 03:48.800
And I thought,

03:48.802 --> 03:51.292
why not the guy who
saved my life in zero G?

03:51.294 --> 03:53.028
(LAUGHS)

03:53.030 --> 03:55.256
Yeah, well, I'm happy to take
a look at your medical records.

03:55.258 --> 03:58.193
- (WHISTLE BLOWS)
- That's me. Good looking out.

03:58.195 --> 04:00.088
I'll let you know if I find anything.

04:02.557 --> 04:03.574
Buckle up.

04:03.576 --> 04:05.599
This may just be a practice game,

04:05.601 --> 04:08.654
but these boys are
about to put on a show.

04:08.656 --> 04:11.248
Ball. Box.

04:12.493 --> 04:15.419
<i>♪ La, la, la, la, la, la ♪</i>

04:15.421 --> 04:17.087
<i>♪ La, la, la, la, la, la, la ♪</i>

04:17.089 --> 04:20.281
<i>♪ La, la, la, la, la, la ♪</i>

04:20.283 --> 04:21.925
<i>♪ Nah-nah-nah-nah-nah-nah-nah, hey! ♪</i>

04:21.927 --> 04:24.744
<i>♪ La, la, la, la, la, la ♪</i>

04:24.746 --> 04:27.170
<i>♪ La, la, la, la, la, la, la... ♪</i>

04:27.172 --> 04:28.779
His footwork's insane.

04:28.781 --> 04:32.019
That's why Dax is the best
rookie this team's ever had.

04:39.278 --> 04:40.519
I need help.

04:40.521 --> 04:42.404
(GROANING)

04:45.693 --> 04:48.494
All right, I got you, I got you.

04:50.790 --> 04:52.647
- Oh! Aah!
- All right.

04:52.649 --> 04:54.649
Your ribs are fractured
in several places.

04:54.651 --> 04:56.627
Your chest wall is unstable.

04:56.629 --> 05:00.113
- We need to get Dax to a hospital.
- REGGIE: I'll call 911.

05:00.115 --> 05:02.154
♪♪

05:02.156 --> 05:04.656
